		"Name": "Broadside",
		"Details": "Developed by Iroquois Machinery Limited as their first entry into true BattleMech production, the Broadside has been met with heavy skepticism by Davion MechWarriors. However, after an impressive showing from a cadet in the 1st Conroe Training Battalion against a Kuritan Atlas, the Broadside is coming to be more broadly accepted. The design is built around a 300-rated fusion engine with Endo-Steel bones and Triple Strength Myomer for extra power. True to its Davion roots, the Broadside uses a mixture of autocannons for primary firepower, a pair of Autocannon/10s and an Autocannon/5 in this case in order to make use of alternative munitions. For backup, the Broadside carries a small number of ER Medium Lasers. The dense armor provides more than enough protection while CASE II protects the substantial ammunition bins.",
		"Icon": "uixTxrIcon_broadside"
	},
